		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Roche limit</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="dablink">This article is about the distance an orbiting object will form rings.  For the limits at which an orbiting object will be captured, see <a href="/wiki/Roche_lobe" title="Roche lobe">Roche lobe</a>.  For the <a href="/wiki/Gravity" title="Gravity" class="mw-redirect">gravitational</a> sphere of influence of one <a href="/wiki/Astronomical_body" title="Astronomical body" class="mw-redirect">astronomical body</a> in the face of perturbations from another heavier body around which it <a href="/wiki/Orbit" title="Orbit">orbits</a>, see <a href="/wiki/Roche_sphere" title="Roche sphere" class="mw-redirect">Roche sphere</a>.</div>
<table width="300" align="right" style="margin-left:15px;">
